main event: A civilian in Kansas City, Missouri reported seeing a single unidentified object in the sky for 20 minutes on December 5, 1952.
interesting points: The object was round and basketball-sized in appearance.
The object was observed moving from east to west at an altitude of approximately 5,000 feet.
Multiple radar contacts were recorded, providing detailed angular positioning data for the object.
The report states that there was 'INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR EVALUATION' in the conclusion.
The report was relayed from the Kansas City Air Route Traffic Control Center to the Lowry Flight Service Center.
